Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Grocery anchored mixed use retail/office development serving London’s southeast quadrant. Various Units available including 12,346 SF of office (divisible to approximately 6,000 SF), 30,000 SF of retail (divisible to approximately 8,000 SF), and potential to build a 7,000 SF pad site (divisible to approximately 1,500 SF). Located at major arterial roadways with immediate proximity to Highway 401. 32,000 vehicles daily along Commissioners Road East and 48,000 daily along Highbury Avenue. Site features Food Basics, Dollarama and Tim Horton’s. Abundant parking and wide variety of possible uses. Leasehold inducements available for qualified tenants. Redevelopment potential for larger tenant seeking specific accommodations.

End cap unit available in a grocery anchored plaza at the corner of Trafalgar Street and Highbury Avenue North. Only one unit remaining with 9,357 SF available, and potential to demise to approximately 3,000 SF and 6,000 SF. The unit is located on the east end of the building, offering exposure to busy Highbury Avenue North (37,000 vehicle per day). Daily traffic counts along Trafalgar Street are approximately 16,000 vehicles. Tenants in the plaza include Fresh Co, Dollarama and Surplus Furniture. The unit features a dock door, two small offices, male and female washrooms. CSA2 zoning allows for various retail, medical, office and recreational uses. Pylon signage available for a monthly fee.

Two small inexpensive units for either Retail and office uses available for lease on ground floor of 3 storey apartment building. Unit 1468 is 648 sq. ft. @ $756 per month and unit 1464 is 897 sq. ft. @ $1,047 per month all inclusive except hydro & HST. All units have a sign band over the store, and face Beckworth Ave. Free on-site parking. See Document Tab for Feature Sheet on all spaces.

Busy plaza on the corner of Southdale and Adelaide Street. Traffic counts of 16,000 vehicles per day along Southdale road. Dollarama in the same complex and in close proximity to Shopper's Drug Mart, Tim Horton's and Paramount Fine Foods. Three units available - 1,630 sq. ft. end cap (unit A) and 1,670 (unit A1) - can be combined for 3,300 sq. ft. - and 1,500 sq. ft. inline unit (unit 12). Additional rent is $9.00 PSF. Utilities separately metered and at the Tenant's expense.

Busy plaza on the corner of Southdale And Adelaide Street. 1,500 sq.ft. unit available. Traffic counts of 16,000 vehicles per day along Southdale Rd. Dollarama in the same complex and in close proximity to Shopper's Drug Mart, Tim Horton's and Paramount Fine Foods.

High profile sublease opportunity at the corner of the space with high exposure to both Wellington Road and Exeter Road. Sublease available until June 30, 2027. The entire space was just built out in 2017 and shows very well. Rear shipping door for access to the warehouse. Possession flexible.

9,000 SF and 11,500 SF Pad Sites available within an established plaza. Located on the south west corner of Exeter Road and Wellington Road South with exposure to over 39,000 vehicles per day along Wellington Road South and 26,000 along Exeter Road. Anchor Tenant to the plaza is Winners, other co-tenant's include Bumper to Bumper, Penningtons, George Richards, Factory Direct, Home Run Sports and a gym (coming soon). Ample on-site parking included. Excellent access / exposure to Highway 401. Public transportation within walking distance.

Various sized retail/office units available at Oxbury Centre. Located on the S/W corner of Oxford St. E. and Highbury Ave. N. with exposure to over 30,000 vehicles per day along Oxford and 36,000 along Highbury. Close proximity to Fanshawe College and a short drive to the downtown core. Recent upgrades include new façade and pylon signage. Units from 450 SF up to 23,743 SF contiguous. Multiple public transit bus stops and access points to the site off of Oxford St., Highbury Ave., and Mornington Ave. Ample on-site free parking. Covered garage along Mornington Ave. Co-tenants include Food Basic, Planet Fitness, Dollarama, Oxbury Pharmacy. Pad sites also available.

4,831 sq.ft. of retail space on the south west corner of Bradley Avenue and Ernest Avenue. Open concept space (currently no offices built out). Anchor Tenant to the plaza is Food Basics. Zoning permits a wide range of uses including (but not limited to) bake shop, clinic, daycare, financial institution, home and auto supply, office, personal service and retail. Traffic counts of 15,500 vehicles per day along Bradley Avenue. Existing inventory (excluding leased items) must be purchased at an agreed upon price before occupancy date.

400 York offers ground floor retail and professional office space on the corner of York and Colborne. This high traffic area will provide great exposure for your business with on-site parking as well as public parking across the street. Second floor office boasts plenty of natural light and can be demised.

Street parking and within walking distance to public transit. Zoned Convenience Commercial - suitable for convenience stores, financial institutions and personal service establishments. Special provision allows for eat-in restaurant.

Address includes 380 Wellington Street. Situated in the heart of downtown London, City Centre is a first class location for business of any size. Modern amenities and building systems, stunning office environments set the backdrop for some of London's most dynamic companies. With shopping, retail, food service and public transportation all within three minutes of your office desk, you can understand why City Centre continues to set the standard of business.

Excellent opportunity for eateries, medical, dental, retail and personal services. Additional Ground Floor offerings available: Suite 09 – 1,163 SF, Suite 4 – 2,339 SF, Suite 22 – 1,252 SF, Suite 35 – 771 SF

Class A office offering within the heart of downtown London. Two levels of underground parking and surface parking available. Modern amenities and building systems, with a stunning lobby and office environment. Onsite retail services, a covered skyway to the Convention centre and Hilton Hotel, and quick access to public transportation. Up to 70,000 SF of office space available at the top of 275 Dundas with great views of the city.

Former Nicholas & Elizabeth Bridal space. 3,000 Sq. Ft. of retail space on the north side of Dundas Street, just east of Wellington Street and beside Crabby Joe's. City parking directly in front of the unit along Dundas. Utilities separately metered and at the Tenant's expense. Zoning permits a wide range of uses, contact listing agent for details.

High profile corner retail location in Downtown London. First time this location has come available in over 20 years: Excellent convenience store location, and lends itself to many other uses. Available January 1 2022. 3,854 SF at the corner of Wellington and Dundas Street Main and lower unit also listed for sale under MLS#40152635

Downtown Retail/Office for lease in the commercial corridor. 166 Dundas Street is located on the Northwest corner of Dundas and Richmond Street and has exterior signage opportunity providing maximum exposure. Retail space includes the main and second floor. The second floor of this loft style retail space is accessed via escalator on the main floor. 3rd, 4th and 5th Floors are office spaces @ $11.95 PSF Net.

Brand new 7,180 sq.ft. commercial development in South London with potential for drive thru. High profile location with daily traffic counts of 34,500 (Southdale Rd.E.)and 29,500 (Wharncliffe Rd.S.) Zoned RSC, permitted uses include clinics, commercial recreation, personal service, convenience service, financial institution, restaurant and more. Located in a actively growing residential / commercial area.

1,200 Sq. Ft. retail unit in the heart of London along Dundas flex Street. Located on the N/E corner of Dundas Street and Talbot Street near Budweiser Gardens, Covent Garden market and other retailers. Recently renovated to a ‘white box’ condition – ready for Tenant build outs. New drop ceiling, furnace, plumbing and electrical panel updated. Large/dry usable basement included for storage. Lease rate is $20.00 per sq. ft net and $4.20 Per sq. ft. for additional rent (Property taxes, Building insurance and HVAC Maintenance).

Class A office building located in the core for lease. Located beside the courthouse and across the street from Budweiser Gardens. The well-known Bell building on the corner of Dundas and Talbot has the lower concourse available with 32,185 sq.ft. and the 6th level offers 5,716 sq.ft. of office space. On site underground parking available.

Great signage and street-front exposure to 37,000 vehicles daily on Oxford Street East. Premises are located on the ground floor of apartment building, just west of Richmond Street beside Urban Outfitters at the north end of Richmond Row. Building has its own 3 level parking garage with controlled entry and a total of 178 parking spaces. Unit 104a - 824 SF is open area (former driving school), Unit 104b-1,372 SF medical office available Aug 31, Unit 108 (former Cycles London) is 1,883 SF with front showroom rear service area. Tenants pay for their own hydro (electric heat/AC unit) See Sales Brochure link for Feature Sheet and floor plans or call Barry Poley @ 519-286-2015 or barry.poley@cbre.com.

Unit 107 consists of 1,635 SF and is a nicely finished open area "operating" light-menu cafe-style restaurant (Carib Shack) with type "B" residential vent for electric stove. Premises front directly onto south side of Oxford with street front & sign visibility to 37,000 vehicles daily. On-site parking garage available at $80.00/space plus multiple metered parking spaces in the immediate area. Possession tied to Lease Surrender with existing tenant. Located just west of Urban Outfitters at Richmond & Oxford. See Sales Brochure link for floor plans, pictures & Feature Sheet. *Possession Remarks Continued: by Tenant
